00:12:56.400 --> 00:12:58.440
So, why do you get a power law

00:12:58.440 --> 00:13:00.573
from the simple St. Petersburg setup?

00:13:01.890 --> 00:13:03.870
If you look at the payout x,

00:13:03.870 --> 00:13:05.790
you can see it grows exponentially

00:13:05.790 --> 00:13:07.590
with each toss of the coin,

00:13:07.590 --> 00:13:09.540
x equals two to the n.

00:13:09.540 --> 00:13:12.330
But if you look at the
probability of tossing the coin

00:13:12.330 --> 00:13:14.160
that many times to get a heads,

00:13:14.160 --> 00:13:17.670
you can see that this probability
shrinks exponentially.

00:13:17.670 --> 00:13:20.100
So the probability of
flipping a coin n times

00:13:20.100 --> 00:13:22.260
is 1/2 to the power of n.

00:13:22.260 --> 00:13:24.720
But we're not really interested
in the number of tosses,

00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:26.400
we're interested in the payout.

00:13:26.400 --> 00:13:28.530
Now we know that x equals two to the n,

00:13:28.530 --> 00:13:29.970
so instead of writing two to the n

00:13:29.970 --> 00:13:31.230
in our probability equation,

00:13:31.230 --> 00:13:32.940
we can just write x.

00:13:32.940 --> 00:13:34.617
So we end up with this,

00:13:34.617 --> 00:13:36.870
the probability of a payout of x dollars

00:13:36.870 --> 00:13:38.700
is equal to one over x,

00:13:38.700 --> 00:13:42.390
or in other words, x to
the power of negative one.

00:13:42.390 --> 00:13:44.250
- You put them together,

00:13:44.250 --> 00:13:47.310
the exponentials conspire
to make a power law.

00:13:47.310 --> 00:13:49.440
And that's a very common thing in nature,

00:13:49.440 --> 00:13:51.330
that a lot of times
when we see power laws,

00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:53.700
there are two underlying exponentials

00:13:53.700 --> 00:13:57.540
that are dancing together
to make a power law.

00:13:57.540 --> 00:13:59.790
- One example of this is earthquakes.

00:13:59.790 --> 00:14:01.260
If you look at data on earthquakes,

00:14:01.260 --> 00:14:03.990
you find that small
earthquakes are very common,

00:14:03.990 --> 00:14:06.330
but earthquakes of increasing magnitudes

00:14:06.330 --> 00:14:09.090
become exponentially rarer.

00:14:09.090 --> 00:14:10.860
But the destruction that earthquakes cause

00:14:10.860 --> 00:14:12.870
is not proportional to their magnitude,

00:14:12.870 --> 00:14:15.270
it's proportional to
the energy they release.

00:14:15.270 --> 00:14:17.490
And as earthquakes grow in magnitude,

00:14:17.490 --> 00:14:20.010
that energy grows exponentially.

00:14:20.010 --> 00:14:21.600
- So there's this exponential decay

00:14:21.600 --> 00:14:24.900
in frequency of earthquakes
of a given magnitude

00:14:24.900 --> 00:14:29.610
and an exponential increase in
the amount of energy released

00:14:29.610 --> 00:14:31.770
by earthquakes of a certain magnitude.

00:14:31.770 --> 00:14:34.620
So when you combine those two exponentials

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:36.060
to eliminate the magnitude,

00:14:36.060 --> 00:14:38.670
what you find is a power law.

00:14:38.670 --> 00:14:40.860
- But power laws also
reveal something deeper

00:14:40.860 --> 00:14:43.230
about the underlying
structure of a system.

00:14:43.230 --> 00:14:44.370
To see this in action,

00:14:44.370 --> 00:14:46.040
let's go back to the third coin game

00:14:46.040 --> 00:14:48.510
and the St. Petersburg paradox.

00:14:48.510 --> 00:14:50.430
Now, you can draw all
the different outcomes

00:14:50.430 --> 00:14:51.630
as a tree diagram

00:14:51.630 --> 00:14:54.780
where the length of each branch
is equal to its probability.

00:14:54.780 --> 00:14:56.850
So starting with a
single line of length one

00:14:56.850 --> 00:14:59.040
and then 1/2 for the first two branches,

00:14:59.040 --> 00:15:01.440
1/4 for the next four, and so on.

00:15:01.440 --> 00:15:03.120
Now, when you zoom in,

00:15:03.120 --> 00:15:05.490
you keep seeing the
same structure repeating

00:15:05.490 --> 00:15:07.440
at smaller and smaller scales.

00:15:07.440 --> 00:15:10.020
It's self-similar like a fractal,

00:15:10.020 --> 00:15:12.000
and that's no coincidence.

00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:15.120
We see the same fractal-like
pattern in the veins on a leaf,

00:15:15.120 --> 00:15:18.150
river networks, the blood
vessels in our lungs,

00:15:18.150 --> 00:15:19.350
even lightning,

00:15:19.350 --> 00:15:20.790
and in all of these cases,

00:15:20.790 --> 00:15:23.940
we can describe the
pattern with a power law.

00:15:23.940 --> 00:15:26.970
Power laws and fractals
are intrinsically linked.

00:15:26.970 --> 00:15:29.820
That's because power laws
reveal something fundamental

00:15:29.820 --> 00:15:31.740
about a system's structure.

00:15:31.740 --> 00:15:34.140
- So I've got a magnet
and I've got a screw,

00:15:34.140 --> 00:15:36.570
