00:15:50.968 --> 00:15:54.480
You see, you heat it up and
suddenly it becomes nonmagnetic.

00:15:54.480 --> 00:15:55.740
To find out what happened,

00:15:55.740 --> 00:15:58.050
let's zoom in on this magnet.

00:15:58.050 --> 00:15:59.010
- Inside a magnet,

00:15:59.010 --> 00:16:01.230
each atom has its own magnetic moment,

00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:02.310
which means you can think of it

00:16:02.310 --> 00:16:04.650
like its own little magnet or compass.

00:16:04.650 --> 00:16:06.630
If one atom's moment points up,

00:16:06.630 --> 00:16:08.670
its neighbors tend to point that way too

00:16:08.670 --> 00:16:11.580
since this lowers the system's
overall potential energy.

00:16:11.580 --> 00:16:12.960
Therefore at low temperatures,

00:16:12.960 --> 00:16:15.000
you get large regions called domains

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:17.370
where all the moments align.

00:16:17.370 --> 00:16:19.560
And when many of these domains also align,

00:16:19.560 --> 00:16:21.870
their individual magnetic fields reinforce

00:16:21.870 --> 00:16:24.930
to create an overall
field around the magnet.

00:16:24.930 --> 00:16:26.550
But if you heat up the magnet,

00:16:26.550 --> 00:16:29.010
each atom starts vibrating vigorously.

00:16:29.010 --> 00:16:31.110
The moments flip up and down

00:16:31.110 --> 00:16:33.750
and so the alignment can break down.

00:16:33.750 --> 00:16:35.460
And when all the moments cancel out,

00:16:35.460 --> 00:16:38.760
then there's no longer
a net magnetic field.

00:16:38.760 --> 00:16:40.230
Now, if you have the right equipment,

00:16:40.230 --> 00:16:42.420
you can balance any magnetic material

00:16:42.420 --> 00:16:44.280
right on that transition point,

00:16:44.280 --> 00:16:47.040
right between magnetic and nonmagnetic.

00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:48.930
This is called the critical point

00:16:48.930 --> 00:16:51.150
and it occurs at a specific temperature

00:16:51.150 --> 00:16:53.160
called the Curie temperature.

00:16:53.160 --> 00:16:55.770
I asked Casper and the
team to build a simulation

00:16:55.770 --> 00:16:58.350
to show what's going on inside the magnet

00:16:58.350 --> 00:16:59.643
at this critical point.

00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:02.700
- Each pixel represents
the magnetic moment

00:17:02.700 --> 00:17:04.020
of an individual atom.

00:17:04.020 --> 00:17:07.020
