00:17:07.020 --> 00:17:08.670
Now, when the temperature is low,

00:17:08.670 --> 00:17:10.230
we get these big domains

00:17:10.230 --> 00:17:12.660
where the magnetic moments are all aligned

00:17:12.660 --> 00:17:15.150
and you get an overall magnetic field.

00:17:15.150 --> 00:17:17.760
But if we really crank up the temperature,

00:17:17.760 --> 00:17:20.130
then all of these moments
start flipping up and down

00:17:20.130 --> 00:17:23.850
and so they cancel out and the
magnet loses its magnetism,

00:17:23.850 --> 00:17:26.700
so that's exactly what
happened in our demo.

00:17:26.700 --> 00:17:29.280
But if we tune the temperature just right,

00:17:29.280 --> 00:17:31.380
