00:32:54.510 --> 00:32:56.130
Similarly here,

00:32:56.130 --> 00:32:58.440
there are people that have
looked at these phenomena

00:32:58.440 --> 00:33:00.000
that go to the critical state,

00:33:00.000 --> 00:33:03.120
in this case it's
self-organized criticality,

00:33:03.120 --> 00:33:05.070
is it brings itself there,

00:33:05.070 --> 00:33:07.890
and what they find is that
there's this universal behavior

00:33:07.890 --> 00:33:11.370
where it doesn't even really
matter what the subparts are,

00:33:11.370 --> 00:33:14.760
you just get the behavior
that's the exact same.

00:33:14.760 --> 00:33:16.410
- At that critical point

00:33:16.410 --> 00:33:18.750
when all the forces are poised

00:33:18.750 --> 00:33:21.240
and the system is right
on that delicate balance

00:33:21.240 --> 00:33:24.360
between being organized, highly organized,

00:33:24.360 --> 00:33:26.160
or being totally disorganized,

00:33:26.160 --> 00:33:29.820
it turns out that almost
none of the physical details

00:33:29.820 --> 00:33:33.810
about that system matter
to how it behaves.

00:33:33.810 --> 00:33:37.290
There's just a universal
behavior that is irrespective

00:33:37.290 --> 00:33:39.840
of what physical system
you're talking about.

00:33:39.840 --> 00:33:42.810
The term that was used
is called universality,

00:33:42.810 --> 00:33:44.100
and it's kind of a miracle,

00:33:44.100 --> 00:33:47.340
it means you can make
extremely powerful theories

00:33:47.340 --> 00:33:49.470
without involving any technical details,

00:33:49.470 --> 00:33:52.080
any real details of the material.

00:33:52.080 --> 00:33:54.150
- What this means is that
you could have these systems

00:33:54.150 --> 00:33:57.240
that on the surface
