You know, floods for example,

00:36:11.880 --> 00:36:12.870
there are a lot of small floods,

00:36:12.870 --> 00:36:15.120
and then every once in a
while, there's a huge one.

00:36:15.120 --> 00:36:17.403
One response to this is insurance,

00:36:18.420 --> 00:36:21.510
that insurance is designed precisely

00:36:21.510 --> 00:36:24.300
to protect you against
the large rare events

00:36:24.300 --> 00:36:25.770
that would otherwise be very bad.

00:36:25.770 --> 00:36:29.310
But then there's the other
side of that picture,

00:36:29.310 --> 00:36:31.620
which is you are the insurance company

00:36:31.620 --> 00:36:33.540
that needs to insure people

00:36:33.540 --> 00:36:35.520
and they have a particularly difficult job

00:36:35.520 --> 00:36:39.750
because they have to be able
to say how much to charge

00:36:39.750 --> 00:36:41.580
so that they have enough money to pay out

00:36:41.580 --> 00:36:44.070
when the big bad thing comes along.

00:36:44.070 --> 00:36:44.903
- [Derek] In 2018,

