So just like that, the company went bust.

00:37:04.920 --> 00:37:07.890
- But while extreme events
can cripple some companies,

00:37:07.890 --> 00:37:09.870
there are entire industries

00:37:09.870 --> 00:37:12.600
that are built on power law distributions.

00:37:12.600 --> 00:37:15.630
Between 1985 and 2014,

00:37:15.630 --> 00:37:17.580
private equity firm Horsley Bridge

00:37:17.580 --> 00:37:20.220
invested in 7,000 different startups

00:37:20.220 --> 00:37:23.070
and over half of their
investments actually lost money,

00:37:23.070 --> 00:37:26.400
but the top 6% more than 10xed in value

00:37:26.400 --> 00:37:29.790
and generated 60% of the
firm's overall profit.

00:37:29.790 --> 00:37:31.740
In fact, the best venture capital firms

00:37:31.740 --> 00:37:34.200
often have more investments
that lose money,

00:37:34.200 --> 00:37:36.540
they just have a few crazy outliers

00:37:36.540 --> 00:37:38.430
that show extraordinary growth,

00:37:38.430 --> 00:37:41.640
a few outliers that carry
the entire performance.

00:37:41.640 --> 00:37:46.380
In 2012, Y Combinator calculated
